<P>Thirty percent of U.S. households have made at least one online purchase since October 1998.  Of the people who buy online, 19 percent purchase electronic goods, according to a 1998 Ernst &amp; Young study.  E-commerce sales keep escalating, creating new business paradigms for the consumer technology industry.  </P>
<P>CEA, the sponsor, producer and manager of CES, is expanding the industry’s growth opportunities created by the Internet. As the premier technology education and networking event, CES offers more than 140 conference sessions with more than 300 expert speakers, including several on e-commerce issues. And, as the showcase for the who, what, where and why of buying and selling, CES will have a special <a href="../../Exhb/pavillions/welcome.cfm">pavilion</a> dedicated to retailing and the Internet.  America Online is one of the many top Internet players you’ll find on the CES show floor.</P>
<P>CEA, the sponsor, producer and manager of CES, also has a dedicated Web site, <a href="http://www.RetailWeb.org"><i>www.RetailWeb.org</I></a>, for e-commerce issues and news.  But for the latest news come January, CES will be the place to be.</P>
